%% Data Flow Diagram for vllm-gaudi
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Router
    participant Gateway as KServe Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant API as vllm-gaudi API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Worker as HPUWorker<br/>HPUModelRunner
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>PCIe/Device
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>S3/PVC/HuggingFace<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over API,Storage: Flow 2: Model Loading (Startup)
    API->>Storage: HTTPS/443 Download model weights<br/>Auth: IAM/Token, TLS 1.2+
    Storage-->>API: Model artifacts
    API->>Worker: Load model to HPU
    Worker->>HPU: Transfer weights to device memory<br/>PCIe/Device

    Note over Client,HPU: Flow 1: Model Inference Request
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Token Auth
    Gateway->>API: HTTP/8000 (TLS terminated)<br/>Token forwarded
    API->>Worker: Prepare inputs (bucketing)
    Worker->>HPU: Forward pass (attention + ops)<br/>PCIe/Device
    HPU-->>Worker: Inference result
    Worker-->>API: Generated tokens
    API-->>Gateway: HTTP/8000 JSON Response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS/443 Completion Response

    Note over Worker,HPU: Flow 3: Distributed Inference (Multi-HPU)
    participant Ray as Ray Head<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Worker2 as HPU Worker N<br/>HCCL

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/completions<br/>HTTPS/443
    Gateway->>API: HTTP/8000
    API->>Ray: Distribute work<br/>Ray protocol/dynamic ports
    Ray->>Worker: Assign shard 0
    Ray->>Worker2: Assign shard N
    Worker->>Worker2: All-reduce/All-gather<br/>HCCL/dynamic ports
    Worker2-->>Worker: Aggregated result
    Worker-->>API: Final output
    API-->>Gateway: JSON Response
    Gateway-->>Client: Completion Response
